properties.areaDesc: Greater Portland Metro Area; Greater Vancouver Area; Lower Columbia and I - 5 Corridor in Cowlitz County; Lower Columbia; Central Willamette Valley; South  Willamette Valley
properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued January 9 at 3:08PM PST until January 11 at 4:00AM PST by NWS Portland OR
properties.description:
* WHAT...South winds 15 to 25 mph with gusts 35 to 45 mph, with
the strongest winds over exposed hills.

* WHERE...In Washington, I-5 Corridor in Cowlitz County and
Greater Vancouver Area. In Oregon, Lower Columbia, Greater
Portland Metro Area, Central Willamette Valley and South
Willamette Valley.

* WHEN...From 1 PM Friday to 4 AM PST Saturday.

* IMPACTS...Gusty winds could blow around unsecured objects. Tree
limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may result.
Saturated soils along with gusty winds can increase the chances
for larger trees to fall over.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...There will be two periods of higher winds,
the first on Friday afternoon and the second on Friday evening
into early Saturday morning.
properties.instruction:
Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high
profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.

Historically, after a period of very heavy rainfall and saturated
soils, wind speeds similar to what is expected with this storm
has caused property damage and power outages from fallen trees.
Residents and businesses are urged to take appropriate actions to
protect their property.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 1 PM FRIDAY TO 4 AM PST SATURDAY
